### 질문: How do I make an HTTP request in Javascript?### 답변: In JavaScript, you can make HTTP requests using the built-in `XMLHttpRequest` object or the newer `fetch` API. Here are examples of both:

Using XMLHttpRequest:
```javascript
const xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open('GET', 'https://example.com/api/data');
xhr.onload = () => {
  console.log(xhr.responseText);
};
xhr.send();
```
Using fetch:
```javascript
fetch('https://example.com/api/data')
  .then(response => response.text())
  .then(data => console.log(data));
```
Both examples perform a GET request to the specified URL and log the response data to the console. Note that in the fetch example, the response is returned as a promise, which is then converted to text using the `.text()` method.

